<h2>About Our Teachers:</h2>

<p>Teachers at choolhouse work in cross-curricular small learning communities focused on career pathways.  
Students complete both career pathway certificate programs and a-g requirements for college.  
Faculty and staff should possess knowledge, understanding, and/or willingness to work in a small learning community. </p>
</br>
<p> Staff is working toward the following goals:</p>
 <ul> 
   <li>Commitment to be a professional learner with interest in co-teaching/planning/learning/reflecting with colleagues/consultants</li>
    <li>Commitment to consensus building and distributed leadership</li>
    <li>Commitment to equal access to high level of instruction for all students</li>
    <li>Commitment to using an inclusion model</li>
    <li>Commitment to making choices based on what students need regardless of what is easiest/most convenient for adults</li>
    <li>Develop academically supportive relationships with students</li>
    <li>Excited about developing strong personal relationships with students</li>
    <li>Flexibility to work outside the box/create a new box and think of new ways to incorporate learning to include all students</li>
    
    <li>Use a progressive discipline plan in conjunction with strong, clear, consistent expectations for classroom behavior</li>
    <li>Use of best practices (balanced literacy, Zone of Proximal Development, Camborne's Conditions of learning)</li>
    <li>Use of on-going formative and summative assessment</li>
    <li>Willing to explore different learning styles of your students</li>
    <li>Willingness to work on a team (develop advisory curriculum, prepare for CAHSEE, work on college prep) and collaborate openly with colleagues</li>
	</ul>
 
